# gom-2.0.alpha

This is a new implementation from scratch of libgom as the 2.0 API/ABI.

It provides a much more complete surface area for an object mapper than
I was able to achieve for the GOM 1.0 series. Backed by years of having
worked on actual databases and concurrency toolkits lead me down a much
different direction this time around.

- Public API surface is naturally asynchronous built on top of DexFuture
  from libdex (my concurrency toolkit).
- Support for Python through GObject Introspection, particularly with
  the help of Gom.py and Dex.py GI overrides installed with their
  respective projects.
- Supports both SQLite and PostgreSQL, though much more biased towards
  SQLite in terms of feature set. Capabilities are dynamic as well as
  compiled, where necessary. It may be possible to add more database
  drivers in the future.
- GomRepository, like the 1.0 ABI, is the primary entry point for
  application develers. GomAdapter hsa been renamed to GomDriver and
  expanded greatly in terms of surface area.
- Transaction scoped APIs are provided in the form of GomSession which
  was completely lacking in the 1.0.
- Native GomExpression tree representation for more semantic
  query generation.
- Asynchronous cursor iteration via GomCursor. We try to hide how
  annoying that can become by providing handy list-models.
- You can materialize to a generic GomRecord if you do not have an
  entity type to materialize. Helpful when reflecting upon an existing
  database which is not mapped into libgom-2 native constructs
  such as a SQLite explorer application.
- Schema-aware query builders for SELECT
- Mutation builders for INSERT, UPDATE, and DELETE which can work on
  GomEntity or raw relations/projections.
- Entity property mapping provides many more features, especially around
  lifecycle and change tracking.
- CRUD helpres for insert/update/delete workflows
- Relationship metadata is now modeled which allows for proper
  one-to-one, one-to-many, many-to-many, inverse, and self-referential
relationships.
- Automatic schema migration for entities, manual schema migration
  integration when you need it.
- Schema introspection with relation listing and relation description
- GTK-facing GListModel adapters: GomQueryModel, GomRelatedModel,
  GomEntityListModel, and GomRecordListModel.
- SQLite driver supports encryption, full-text search (FTS5), and vector
  search via vec1.
- Abstractions for synchronization with external system in the form of
  GomSyncCoordinator and GomSyncTransport. The long-term goal here is to
  provide the necessary mechanics for continual sync to a personal data-
  store that is not necessarliy on-device but could be local-network,
  or even a hosted service.
